title._content: Astronaut C. Michael Foale prepares to don a Mark III advanced space suit technology demonstrator

description._content: Collection: NASA Human Spaceflight Collection General Description: Exploration Imagery Description: JSC2006-E-23367 (14 June 2006) --- Attired in his thermal undergarment, astronaut C. Michael Foale prepares to don a Mark III advanced space suit technology demonstrator as he participates in a 10-kilometer extravehicular activity (EVA) "walk-back" test in the pogo test area of the Space Vehicle Mockup Facility at Johnson Space Center. Data collected in the test will be used in development of the next generation of space suits that are being designed for use in the Constellation Program. image id: Photo-jsc2006e23367 UID: SPD-SPFLT-Photo-jsc2 006e23367 original url: spaceflight.nasa.gov/gallery/images/exploration/constella...
